      "side": 1,
      "message": "I haven\u0027t read the whole thing yet, but I had similar concerns.\n\nI would definitely like to come up with a better answer for Layout storage; I\u0027m also not satisfied with this approach. Maybe they could be IRNodes that come out of the pool, or due to their large size, maybe we need a dedicated pool just for Layout nodes. \n\nThis might be the opportunity for us to actually experiment with using a pool class. Do we have anything in Gr/Sk that we can start with? I found GrTBlockList but that is more like a deque than a pool. (TBH I don\u0027t actually see from the GrTBlockList doc-comment how it meaningfully differs from deque for most operations; it\u0027s got better concat and slightly worse random-access, I guess?)",
