      "writtenOn": "2020-10-07T14:23:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How much bloat do we actually incur if we just jam Layout into the IRNode as a stopgap solution for now? Or, if that\u0027s just untenable, how bad would it be to have a unique_ptr\u003cLayout\u003e in the VariableData for now until we have a better/poolable solution? We already know that the current IRNode class is in a halfway state where it\u0027s not as efficient as it will be once we\u0027re through, so I\u0027m not worried about a bit of extra bloat in the short-term as long as we\u0027re confident that the end state will be good. But I am a little concerned about putting in new temporary systems for bloat control that might become difficult to untangle later.",
      "parentUuid": "03769f97_6c7ec689",
      "revId": "bb949f8e875dd80e86eaf7f138b116d2931be055",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
